<br>
Take average teenage boy, lets call him Mad Alias. He starts to draw a lot age 11, stops age 12, comes back to drawing age 13 when his is offically a teenager. He starts to spend some of his money on drawing, he starts to draw quite a lot.<br>
<br>
Within five months he is willing to spend £90 randomly buying a tablet only to go out on every weekend to buy... more sketchbooks, pens, pencils, rubbers and other strange drawing items. Suddenly he starts to attually dream about drawing, and when he wakes thinks that was a good idea for a drawing lets do it.<br>
<br>
Before you know it in one draw he's producing 5 pieces of art, This ladies and gentlemen is what we call OODS or <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Over Obessive Drawing Sindrome</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
